    "body": "Not really. Lookups for a specific ID in node ID space are easy in v5. They were expensive in v4 because the FINDNODE target parameter was a public key and hashed on the node answering the query. In v5 FINDNODE takes a bucket number as parameter (in the current spec draft at least). ",
